HEADWORD: Connaturality
<hw>Con*nat`u*ral"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>Participation of the same nature; natural union or
connection.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A congruity and <qex>connaturality</qex> between them.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir M. Hale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Connaturalize</ent>⟦br⟧
